<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 9600, 9700 AND 9800 SERIES -
        REPLACE - RELAY LEVER BUSHING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
        <title>RELAY LEVER BUSHING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the radiator grille upper panel, the headlamp bezels and the radiator grille lower
                panel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the cab fully forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the control rod return spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the upper (vertical) and lower (horizontal) control rods from the relay lever by
                removing the cotter and yoke pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the yoke pin holes in the upper and lower control rods. If worn, replace the rods.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cotter pin. Remove the relay pivot bolt, retaining nut and flat washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the relay lever, sleeve and pivot bolt from the cab hinge bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100906">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the yoke pin holes in the relay lever. If worn, replace the relay lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a remover tool and support plate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100907">Figure 7</hotlnk>) to press the old bushing from the relay lever. Remover tool
                can be made locally following dimensions shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100908">Figure 8</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100906" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100906" filename="../figg11/g1100906.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Relay Lever Mounting</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CLEVIS PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>2. UPPER ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>3. COTTER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>4. LEVER WITH BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. PIVOT SLEEVE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. PIVOT BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. HINGE BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>8. LOWER ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>9. WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>10. SLOTTED NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100907" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100907" filename="../figg11/g1100907.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Removing Relay Lever Bushing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PRESS RAM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. REMOVER TOOL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RELAY LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SUPPORT PLATE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the new bushing in the relay lever as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the bore of the relay lever and the outside diameter of the bushing with
                    engine oil.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Start the bushing into the chamfered side of the relay shaft bore.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Support the relay lever on a flat surface. Use a driver tool and tool handle ZTSE-2635 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100909">Figure 9</hotlnk>) to press the bushing into relay lever until flush with
                    the edges of the lever.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check the fit of the new pivot sleeve in the bushing. If necessary, lightly hone the
                    bushing to obtain .002 to .006" (.05 to .15 mm) running clearance.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the pivot bolt, pivot sleeve and relay lever on the cab hinge bracket. Install the
                flat washer and retaining nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the relay lever retaining nut to 50 to 60 ft-lbs. (68 to 81 N&#8226;m). Install
                cotter pin. (If necessary, turn the nut slightly to align cotter pin slots with the pin hole in the
                bolt).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the upper and lower control rods to the relay lever with yoke pins. Install new
                cotter pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>The yoke pins must be installed so that the end with the cotter pin hole points outward (toward
                    driver's side of vehicle).
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the return spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lower the cab.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the clutch internal, clutch pedal and release yoke to release bearing clearance
                adjustments and readjust if needed. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s11009r_4.xml" xrefid="hl1100901">ADJUSTMENT
                    <xref refid="hl1100901"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100908" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100908" filename="../figg11/g1100908.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Dimensions for Making Bushing Remover Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100909" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100909" filename="../figg11/g1100909.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Installing Relay Lever Bushing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PRESS RELEASE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TOOL HANDLE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. DRIVER TOOL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BUSHING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RELAY LEVER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
